Class DriverExceptionOld

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
IDescriptableException, java.io.Serializable
public class DriverExceptionOld
extends java.lang.Exception
implements IDescriptableException

A DriverException is thrown if a driver fails. This exception doesn't reports about the cause of the failure, that task is made by its inner ExceptionDescription.

DriverExceptionOld

public DriverExceptionOld(java.lang.String message,
                          java.lang.Throwable cause,
                          ExceptionDescription exceptionType)

Constructs a new DriverException with the specified detail message, cause and the original exception that produced this one. This second exception will have the complete information about the causes.

Note that the detail message associated with the cause is not automatically incorporated in this exception's detail message.

Parameters:
message - the detail message (which is saved for later retrieval calling getMessage()).
cause - the cause (which is saved for later retrieval calling getCause())). (A null value is permitted, and indicates that the cause is nonexistent or unknown.)
exceptionType - detailed information about the cause of this exception
